  "text": "E7 expression in epithelial cells was demonstrated to cause a drop in the levels of the adhesion protein E-cadherin, which is involved in DLG1 localization at cell contacts [CITATION_1] Hellner et al., 2009 ). This may account for the slight decrease in DLG1 immunostaining at cell borders in the presence of HPV-18 E7. Moreover, DLG1 reduction at cell contacts was more striking in E6/E7 cultures. Therefore, it is possible to speculate that E6 could contribute to DLG1 downregulation, perhaps by preferentially targeting those DLG1 forms for degradation (Massimi et al., 2006) .",
